    "Third, upon perceiving a moral situation in which we are to act, we often directly identify what is our moral duty, rather than having to go through a reasoning process.",
    "If we want to determine if strong artificial FMSs are possible, then, we should consider whether AI systems can possess moral sensitivity as characterised here.",
    "To start to answer this question, I will consider two types of AMAs distinguished by Allen et al. (2005): top-down and bottomup AMAs.",
    "Roughly, top-down AMAs are programmed to follow predetermined moral rules, while bottom-up AMAs are programmed to learn moral behaviour from concrete situations. foot_0",
